			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The problem is not that it's &quot;ugly&quot;, it's just not practical. You can only access VRAM during vblank, which lasts about 8% of the time of a frame, so it simply doesn't make sense to cram VRAM updates and collision logic inside such a small slice of time, while a lot of the remaining 92% of the time goes to waste. This may work for really simple games where not much happens each frame, but as you add more objects and more action, this model quickly becomes unfeasible.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

