					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Jun 05, 2005 2:04 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 2149<br /><b>Location:</b> Minneapolis, Minnesota, United States
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Another disadvantage to using hardware tiles for collision detection is that if you do, you really can't repurpose a hardware tile. For example, you can't use the same tile to draw a real wall and a fake wall, even though the graphics are identical. Metatiles have more flexibility this way, and multiple metatile definitions typically takes up less space than multiple hardware tiles (you also have more room to define metatiles in PRG-ROM than you do hardware tiles in CHR-ROM).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
		</tr>

