				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">-Basti- wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One more thing: how do scrolling games handle this? Do they switch between various collision maps according to the position of the player?</div><br />I guess this is done differently for different games.<br /><br />My own game, &quot;City Trouble&quot;, had an array with 34 values: The platform height for each of the 32 visible tiles + the tile left from the screen + the tile right from the screen. (If the scrolling doesn't align to 8 pixels, the part right from the screen is even visible.)<br /><br />Whenever the scrolling aligned to 8 pixels, I shifted the values in the array to the left and loaded the rightmost position with the new value from the general level data.</div>

					
